definitions.definition: The degree to which something fits.
examples: This shirt is a bad fit .
Since he put on weight, his jeans have been a tight fit .

definitions.definition: Conformity of elements one to another.
examples: It's hard to get a good fit using second-hand parts.

definitions.definition: The part of an object upon which anything fits tightly.
( advertising ) Measure of how well a particular commercial execution captures the character or values of a brand.
examples: The Wonder Bread advertising research results showed the “White Picket Fence” commercial had strong fit ratings.

definitions.definition: ( bridge ) The quality of a partnership's combined holding of cards in a suit , particularly of trump .
examples: During the auction, it is often a partnership's goal to find an eight-card major suit fit .

main_definition: The degree to which something fits.
secondary_definitions: Conformity of elements one to another.
The part of an object upon which anything fits tightly.
( advertising ) Measure of how well a particular commercial execution captures the character or values of a brand.
( bridge ) The quality of a partnership's combined holding of cards in a suit , particularly of trump .

definitions.definition: ( archaic ) A section of a poem or ballad .

main_definition: ( archaic ) A section of a poem or ballad .

examples: My grandfather died after having a fit .

definitions.definition: ( medicine ) A sudden and vigorous appearance of a symptom over a short period of time.

examples: He had a laughing fit which lasted more than ten minutes.
She had a fit and threw all of his clothes out through the window.
He threw a fit (of temper ) when his car broke down.

secondary_definitions: ( medicine ) A sudden and vigorous appearance of a symptom over a short period of time.

definitions.definition: An outfit , a set of clothing .
examples: How do you like the fit ?

main_definition: ( slang ) An outfit , a set of clothing .
